"Here is a method in Java to convert a string to title case while handling exception words:

```java
public class TitleCaseConverter {
    // List of exception words that should not be capitalized
    private static final List<String> EXCEPTION_WORDS = List.of("of", "the", "is", "and");

    /**
     * Converts a given string to title case, with exception words handled appropriately.
     * @param input The input string to be converted.
     * @return The converted string in title case.
     * @throws IllegalArgumentException if the input is null or empty.
     */
    public static String convertToTitleCase(String input) {
        if (input == null || input.isEmpty()) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Input cannot be null or empty.");
        }

        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();
        String[] words = input.split("\\s+");

        for (int i = 0; i < words.length; i++) {
            String word = words[i].toLowerCase();
            if (i == 0) {
                // First word is always capitalized
                result.append(word.charAt(0).toUpperCase()).append(word.substring(1));
            } else {
                // Check if the word is an exception word
                if (EXCEPTION_WORDS.contains(word)) {
                    result.append(word);
                } else {
                    result.append(word.charAt(0).toUpperCase()).append(word.substring(1));
                }
            }
        }

        return result.toString();
    }
}
```

### Example Usage:
```java
